INSERT INTO POKEMON VALUES
(1, 'Bulbasaur', 12, 4, 0.7, 6.9, 'Seed', 'For some time after its birth, it uses the nutrients that are packed into the seed on its back in order to grow.'),
(2, 'Ivysaur', 12, 4, 1.0, 13.0, 'Seed', 'The more sunlight Ivysaur bathes in, the more strength wells up within it, allowing the bud on its back to grow larger.'),
(3, 'Venusaur', 12, 4, 2.0, 100.0, 'Seed', 'While it basks in the sun, it can convert the light into energy. As a result, it is more powerful in the summertime.'),
(4, 'Charmander', 10, NULL, 0.6, 8.5, 'Lizard', 'The flame on its tail shows the strength of its life-force. If Charmander is weak, the flame also burns weakly.'),
(5, 'Charmeleon', 10, NULL, 1.1, 19.0, 'Flame', 'When it swings its burning tail, the temperature around it rises higher and higher, tormenting its opponents.'),
(6, 'Charizard', 10, 3, 1.7, 90.5, 'Flame', 'If Charizard becomes truly angered, the flame at the tip of its tail burns in a light blue shade'),
(7, 'Squirtle', 11, NULL, 0.5, 9.0, 'Tiny Turtle', 'After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. It sprays a potent foam from its mouth.'),
(8, 'Wartortle', 11, NULL, 1.0, 22.5, 'Turtle', 'Wartortle''s long, furry tail is a symbol of longevity, so this Pokémon is quite popular among older people.'),
(9, 'Blastoise', 11, NULL, 1.6, 85.5, 'Shelfish', 'It deliberately increases its body weight so it can withstand the recoil of the water jets it fires.'),
(10, 'Caterpie', 7, NULL, 0.3, 2.9, 'Worm', 'For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.'),
(11, 'Metapod', 7, NULL, 0.7, 9.9, 'Cocoon', 'It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.'),
(12, 'Butterfree', 7, 3, 1.1, 32.0, 'Butterfly', 'It loves the nectar of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.'),
(13, 'Weedle', 7, 4, 0.3, 3.2, 'Hairy Bug', 'Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.'),
(14, 'Kakuna', 7, 4, 0.6, 10.0, 'Cocoon', 'Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.'),
(15, 'Beedrill', 7, 4, 1.0, 29.5, 'Poison Bee', 'It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.'),
(16, 'Pidgey', 1, 3, 0.3, 1.8, 'Tiny Bird', 'Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.'),
(17, 'Pidgeotto', 1, 3, 1.1, 30.0, 'Bird', 'This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.'),
(18, 'Pidgeot', 1, 3, 1.5, 39.5, 'Bird', 'This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.'),
(19, 'Rattata', 1, NULL, 0.3, 3.5, 'Mouse', 'Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.'),
(20, 'Raticate', 1, NULL, 0.7, 18.5, 'Mouse', 'Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.'),
(21, 'Spearow', 1, 3, 0.3, 2.0, 'Tiny Bird', 'Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.'),
(22, 'Fearow', 1, 3, 1.2, 38.0, 'Beak', 'A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.'),
(23, 'Ekans', 4, NULL, 2.0, 6.9, 'Snake', 'It can freely detach its jaw to swallow large prey whole. It can become too heavy to move, however.'),
(24, 'Arbok', 4, NULL, 3.5, 65.0, 'Cobra', 'The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.'),
(25, 'Pikachu', 13, NULL, 0.4, 6.0, 'Mouse', 'When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.'),
(26, 'Raichu', 13, NULL, 0.8, 30.0, 'Mouse', 'Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.'),
(27, 'Sandshrew', 5, NULL, 0.6, 12.0, 'Mouse', 'It digs deep burrows to live in. When in danger, it rolls up its body to withstand attacks.'),
(28, 'Sandslash', 5, NULL, 1.0, 29.5, 'Mouse', 'It is adept at attacking with the spines on its back and its sharp claws while quickly scurrying about.'),
(29, 'Nidoran', 4, NULL, 0.4, 7.0, 'Poison Pin', 'Females are more sensitive to smells than males. While foraging, they''ll use their whiskers to check wind direction and stay downwind of predators.'),
(30, 'Nidorina', 4, NULL, 0.8, 20.0, 'Poison Pin', 'The horn on its head has atrophied. It''s thought that this happens so Nidorina''s children won''t get poked while their mother is feeding them.'),
(31, 'Nidoqueen', 4, 5, 1.3, 60.0, 'Drill', 'Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield its children from any kind of attack.'),
(32, 'Nidoran', 4, NULL, 0.5, 9.0, 'Poison Pin', 'The horn on a male Nidoran''s forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.'),
(33, 'Nidorino', 4, NULL, 0.9, 19.5, 'Poison Pin', 'With a horn that''s harder than diamond, this Pokémon goes around shattering boulders as it searches for a moon stone.'),
(34, 'Nidoking', 4, 5, 1.4, 62.0, 'Drill', 'When it goes on a rampage, it''s impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it''s lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.'),
(35, 'Clefairy', 18, NULL, 0.6, 7.5, 'Fairy', 'On nights with a full moon, Clefairy gather from all over and dance. Bathing in moonlight makes them float.'),
(36, 'Clefable', 18, NULL, 1.3, 40.0, 'Fairy', 'Said to live in quiet, remote mountains, this type of fairy has a strong aversion to being seen.'),
(37, 'Vulpix', 10, NULL, 0.6, 9.9, 'Fox', 'If it is attacked by an enemy that is stronger than itself, it feigns injury to fool the enemy and escapes.'),
(38, 'Ninetails', 10, NULL, 1.1, 19.9, 'Fox', 'Some legends claim that each of its nine tails has its own unique type of special mystical power.'),
(39, 'Jigglypuff', 1, 18, 0.5, 5.5, 'Balloon', 'When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.'),
(40, 'Wigglytuff', 1, 18, 1.0, 12.0, 'Balloon', 'It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a body slam.'),
(41, 'Zubat', 4, 3, 0.8, 7.5, 'Bat', 'It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.'),
(42, 'Golbat', 4, 3, 1.6, 55.0, 'Bat', 'It loves to drink other creatures'' blood. It''s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.'),
(43, 'Oddish', 12, 4, 0.5, 5.4, 'Weed', 'Its scientific name is Oddium wanderus. It is said to cover distances as far as 1,000 feet when night falls, walking on its two roots.'),
(44, 'Gloom', 12, 4, 0.8, 8.6, 'Weed', 'The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn''t drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.'),
(45, 'Vileplume', 12, 4, 1.2, 18.6, 'Flower', 'The bud bursts into bloom with a bang. It then starts scattering allergenic, poisonous pollen.'),
(46, 'Paras', 7, 12, 0.3, 5.4, 'Mushroom', 'Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.'),
(47, 'Parasect', 7, 12, 1.0, 29.5, 'Mushroom', 'The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.'),
(48, 'Venonat', 7, 4, 1.0, 30.0, 'Insect', 'Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches small bug Pokémon at night that are attracted by light.'),
(49, 'Venomoth', 7, 4, 1.5, 12.5, 'Poison Moth', 'The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.'),
(50, 'Diglett', 5, NULL, 0.2, 0.8, 'Mole', 'It lives about one yard underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.'),
(51, 'Dugtrio', 5, NULL, 0.7, 33.3, 'Mole', 'Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.'),
(52, 'Meowoth', 1, NULL, 0.4, 4.2, 'Scratch Cat', 'All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.'),
(53, 'Persian', 1, NULL, 1.0, 32.0, 'Classy Cat', 'Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.'),
(54, 'Psyduck', 11, NULL, 0.8, 19.6, 'Duck', 'It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.'),
(55, 'Golduck', 11, NULL, 1.7, 76.6, 'Duck', 'When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.'),
(56, 'Mankey', 2, NULL, 0.5, 28.0, 'Pig Monkey', 'It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.'),
(57, 'Primeape', 2, NULL, 1.0, 32.0, 'Pig Monkey', 'It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.'),
(58, 'Growlithe', 10, NULL, 0.7, 19.0, 'Puppy', 'It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.'),
(59, 'Arcanine', 10, NULL, 1.9, 155.0, 'Legendary', 'An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.'),
(60, 'Poliwag', 11, NULL, 0.6, 12.4, 'Tadpole', 'The swirl on its belly is its insides showing through the skin. It appears more clearly after Poliwag eats.'),
(61, 'Poliwhirl', 11, NULL, 1.0, 20.0, 'Tadpole', 'Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.'),
(62, 'Poliwrath', 11, 2, 1.3, 54.0, 'Tadpole', 'Although it''s skilled in a style of dynamic swimming that uses all its muscles, for some reason it lives on dry land.'),
(63, 'Abra', 14, NULL, 0.9, 19.5, 'Psi', 'This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra''s dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.'),
(64, 'Kadabra', 14, NULL, 1.3, 56.5, 'Psi', 'Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.'),
(65, 'Alakazam', 14, NULL, 1.5, 48.0, 'Psi', 'It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.'),
(66, 'Machop', 2, NULL, 0.8, 19.5, 'Superpower', 'Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it''s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.'),
(67, 'Machoke', 2, NULL, 1.5, 70.5, 'Superpower', 'Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.'),
(68, 'Machamp', 2, NULL, 1.6, 130.0, 'Superpower', 'It punches with its four arms at blinding speed. It can launch 1,000 punches in two seconds.'),
(69, 'Bellsprout', 12, 4, 0.7, 4.0, 'Flower', 'No matter what Bellsprout is doing, if it detects movement nearby, it will immediately react by reaching out with its thin vines.'),
(70, 'Weepinbell', 12, 4, 1.0, 6.4, 'Flycatcher', 'Even though it is filled with acid, it does not melt because it also oozes a protective fluid.'),
(71, 'Victreebel', 12, 4, 1.7, 15.5, 'Flycathcer', 'It lures prey into its mouth with a nectar-like aroma. The helpless prey is melted with a dissolving fluid.'),
(72, 'Tentacool', 11, 4, 0.9, 45.5, 'Jellyfish', 'When the tide goes out, dehydrated Tentacool can be found left behind on the shore.'),
(73, 'Tentacruel', 11, 4, 1.6, 55.0, 'Jellyfish', 'On the rare occasions that large outbreaks of Tentacruel occur, all fish Pokémon disappear from the surrounding sea.'),
(74, 'Geodude', 6, 5, 0.4, 20.0, 'Rock', 'At rest, it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.'),
(75, 'Graveler', 6, 5, 1.0, 105.0, 'Rock', 'A slow walker, it rolls to move. It pays no attention to any object that happens to be in its path.'),
(76, 'Golem', 6, 5, 1.4, 300.0, 'Megaton', 'It is enclosed in a hard shell that is as rugged as slabs of rock. It sheds skin once a year to grow larger.'),
(77, 'Ponyta', 10, NULL, 1.0, 30.0, 'Fire Horse', 'About an hour after birth, Ponyta''s fiery mane and tail grow out, giving the Pokémon an impressive appearance.'),
(78, 'Rapidash', 10, NULL, 1.7, 95.0, 'Fire Horse', 'It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.'),
(79, 'Slowpoke', 11, 14, 1.2, 36.0, 'Dopey', 'It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.'),
(80, 'Slowbro', 11, 14, 1.6, 78.5, 'Hermit Crab', 'When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.'),
(81, 'Magnemite', 13, 9, 0.3, 6.0, 'Magnet', 'The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.'),
(82, 'Magneton', 13, 9, 1.0, 60.0, 'Magnet', 'Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.'),
(83, 'Farfetch''d', 1, 3, 0.8, 15.0, 'Wild Duck', 'It can''t live without the stalk it holds. That''s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.'),
(84, 'Doduo', 1, 3, 1.4, 39.2, 'Twin Bird', 'Its twin heads have exactly the same genes and battle in perfect sync with each other.'),
(85, 'Dotrio', 1, 3, 1.8, 85.2, 'Triple Bird', 'It now has three hearts and three sets of lungs. Though it can''t run as fast as Doduo, Dodrio can keep running for longer stretches of time.'),
(86, 'Seel', 11, NULL, 1.1, 90.0, 'Sea Lion', 'The protrusion on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.'),
(87, 'Dewgong', 11, 15, 1.7, 120.0, 'Sea Lion', 'It sleeps under shallow ocean waters during the day, then looks for food at night when it''s colder.'),
(88, 'Grimer', 4, NULL, 0.9, 30.0, 'Sludge', 'Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.'),
(89, 'Muk', 4, NULL, 1.2, 52.0, 'Sludge', 'It''s thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.'),
(90, 'Shellder', 11, NULL, 0.3, 4.0, 'Bivalve', 'It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.'),
(91, 'Cloyster', 11, 15, 1.5, 132.5, 'Bivalve', 'Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.'),
(92, 'Gastly', 8, 4, 1.3, 0.1, 'Gas', 'It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.'),
(93, 'Haunter', 8, 4, 1.6, 0.1, 'Gas', 'It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.'),
(94, 'Gengar', 8, 4, 1.5, 40.5, 'Shadow', 'To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey''s shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.'),
(95, 'Onix', 6, 5, 8.8, 210.0, 'Rock Snake', 'As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.'),
(96, 'Drowzee', 14, NULL, 1.0, 32.4, 'Hypnosis', 'It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children''s are much tastier.'),
(97, 'Hypno', 14, NULL, 1.6, 75.6, 'Hypnosis', 'When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves, such as Hypnosis and Confusion.'),
(98, 'Krabby', 11, NULL, 0.4, 6.5, 'River Crab', 'It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.'),
(99, 'Kingler', 11, NULL, 1.3, 60.0, 'Pincer', 'The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.'),
(100, 'Voltorb', 13, NULL, 0.5, 10.4, 'Ball', 'It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.'),
(101, 'Electrode', 13, NULL, 1.2, 66.6, 'Ball', 'The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.'),
(102, 'Exeggcute', 12, 14, 0.4, 2.5, 'Egg', 'If you touch one of Exeggcute''s heads, mistaking it for an egg, the other heads will quickly gather and attack you in a swarm.'),
(103, 'Exeggutor', 12, 14, 2.0, 120.0, 'Coconut', 'It is called the Walking Jungle. Each of the nuts has a face and a will of its own.'),
(104, 'Cubone', 5, NULL, 0.4, 6.5, 'Lonely', 'When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.'),
(105, 'Marowak', 5, NULL, 1.0, 45.0, 'Bone Keeper', 'This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.'),
(106, 'Hitmonlee', 2, NULL, 1.5, 49.8, 'Kicking', 'At the exact moment it lands a kick on its target, Hitmonlee hardens the muscles on the sole of its foot, maximizing the power of the kick.'),
(107, 'Hitmonchan', 2, NULL, 1.4, 50.2, 'Punching', 'It corners its foes with combo punches from both sides, then finishes them off with a single straight punch launched at over 300 mph.'),
(108, 'Lickitung', 1, NULL, 1.2, 65.5, 'Licking', 'If this Pokémon''s sticky saliva gets on you and you don''t clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won''t go away, either.'),
(109, 'Koffing', 4, NULL, 0.6, 1.0, 'Poison Gas', 'Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.'),
(110, 'Weezing', 4, NULL, 1.2, 9.5, 'Poison Gas', 'Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the highest level.'),
(111, 'Rhyhorn', 5, 6, 1.0, 115.0, 'Spikes', 'Rhyhorn claims an area with over a six mile radius as its territory. It apparently forgets where this territory is when running, however.'),
(112, 'Rhydon', 5, 6, 1.9, 120.0, 'Drill', 'The horn of a Rhydon is powerful enough to crush raw diamonds. These Pokémon polish their horns by bashing them together.'),
(113, 'Chansey', 1, NULL, 1.1, 34.6, 'Egg', 'This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.'),
(114, 'Tangela', 12, NULL, 1.0, 35.0, 'Vine', 'Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon''s true appearance remains a mystery.'),
(115, 'Kangaskhan', 1, NULL, 2.2, 80.0, 'Parent', 'Although it''s carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.'),
(116, 'Horsea', 11, NULL, 0.4, 8.0, 'Dragon', 'If attacked—even by a large enemy—Horsea effortlessly swims to safety by utilizing its well-developed dorsal fin.'),
(117, 'Seadra', 11, NULL, 1.2, 25.0, 'Dragon', 'The male raises the young. If it is approached while caring for young, it will use its toxic spines to fend off the intruder.'),
(118, 'Goldeen', 11, NULL, 0.6, 15.0, 'Goldfish', 'Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.'),
(119, 'Seaking', 11, NULL, 1.3, 39.0, 'Goldfish', 'In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.'),
(120, 'Staryu', 11, NULL, 0.8, 34.5, 'Star Shape', 'If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you''ll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.'),
(121, 'Starmie', 11, 14, 1.1, 80.0, 'Mysterious', 'This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.'),
(122, 'Mr.Mime', 14, 18, 1.3, 54.5, 'Barrier', 'It is a pantomime expert that can create invisible but solid walls using miming gestures.'),
(123, 'Scyther', 7, 3, 1.5, 56.0, 'Mantis', 'It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.'),
(124, 'Jynx', 15, 14, 1.4, 40.6, 'Human Shape', 'In certain parts of Galar, Jynx was once feared and worshiped as the Queen of Ice.'),
(125, 'Electabuzz', 13, NULL, 1.1, 30.0, 'Electric', 'Its body constantly discharges electricity. Getting close to it will make your hair stand on end.'),
(126, 'Magmar', 10, NULL, 1.3, 44.5, 'Spitfire', 'Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather''s body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.'),
(127, 'Pinsir', 7, NULL, 1.5, 55.0, 'Stag Beetle', 'These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.'),
(128, 'Tauros', 1, NULL, 1.4, 88.4, 'Wild Bull', 'When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.'),
(129, 'Magikarp', 11, NULL, 0.9, 10.0, 'Fish', 'An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.'),
(130, 'Gyarados', 11, 3, 6.5, 235.0, 'Atrocious', 'Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.'),
(131, 'Lapras', 11, 15, 2.5, 220.0, 'Transport', 'It ferries people across the sea on its back. It may sing an enchanting cry if it is in a good mood.'),
(132, 'Ditto', 1, NULL, 0.3, 4.0, 'Transform', 'Its transformation ability is perfect. However, if made to laugh, it can''t maintain its disguise.'),
(133, 'Eevee', 1, NULL, 0.3, 6.5, 'Evolution', 'Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.'),
(134, 'Vaporeon', 11, NULL, 1.0, 29.0, 'Bubble Jet', 'It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid''s.'),
(135, 'Jolteon', 13, NULL, 0.8, 24.5, 'Lightning', 'It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.'),
(136, 'Flareon', 10, NULL, 0.9, 25.0, 'Flame', 'Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.'),
(137, 'Porygon', 1, NULL, 0.8, 36.5, 'Virtual', 'It is an artificial Pokémon. Since it doesn''t breathe, people are excited by its potential to be useful in any environment.'),
(138, 'Omanyte', 6, 11, 0.4, 7.5, 'Spiral', 'Because some Omanyte manage to escape after being restored or are released into the wild by people, this species is becoming a problem.'),
(139, 'Omastar', 6, 11, 1.0, 35.0, 'Spiral', 'Weighed down by a large and heavy shell, Omastar couldn''t move very fast. Some say it went extinct because it was unable to catch food.'),
(140, 'Kabuto', 6, 11, 0.5, 11.5, 'Shellfish', 'This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto molt every three days, making their shells harder and harder.'),
(141, 'Kabutops', 6, 11, 1.3, 40.5, 'Shellfish', 'Kabutops slices its prey apart and sucks out the fluids. The discarded body parts become food for other Pokémon.'),
(142, 'Aerodactyl', 6, 3, 1.8, 59.0, 'Fossil', 'This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times. Apparently even modern technology is incapable of producing a perfectly restored specimen.'),
(143, 'Snorlax', 1, NULL, 2.1, 460.0, 'Sleeping', 'This gluttonous Pokémon eats constantly, apart from when it''s asleep. It devours nearly 900 pounds of food per day.'),
(144, 'Articuno', 15, 3, 1.7, 55.4, 'Freeze', 'This legendary bird Pokémon can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.'),
(145, 'Zapdos', 13, 3, 1.6, 52.6, 'Electric', 'This legendary Pokémon is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.'),
(146, 'Moltres', 10, 3, 2.0, 60.0, 'Flame', 'It is one of the legendary bird Pokémon. Its appearance is said to indicate the coming of spring.'),
(147, 'Dratini', 16, NULL, 1.8, 3.3, 'Dragon', 'It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process, it is protected by a rapid waterfall.'),
(148, 'Dragonair', 16, NULL, 4.0, 16.5, 'Dragon', 'They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.'),
(149, 'Dragonite', 16, 3, 2.2, 210.0, 'Dragon', 'It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.'),
(150, 'Mewtwo', 14, NULL, 2.0, 122.0, 'Genetic', 'Its DNA is almost the same as Mew''s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.'),
(151, 'Mew', 14, NULL, 0.4, 4.0, 'New Species', 'When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon''s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.'),
(152, 'Chikorita', 12, NULL, 0.9, 6.4, 'Leaf', 'It loves to bask in the sunlight. It uses the leaf on its head to seek out warm places.'),
(153, 'Bayleef', 12, NULL, 1.2, 15.8, 'Leaf', 'The spicy scent that wafts from around Bayleef''s neck somehow makes those who smell it want to fight.'), 
(154, 'Meganium', 12, NULL, 1.8, 100.5, 'Herb', 'Anyone who stands beside it becomes refreshed, just as if they were soaking in the soothing atmosphere of a forest.'),
(155, 'Cyndaquil', 10, NULL, 0.5, 7.9, 'Fire Mouse', 'It usually stays hunched over. If it is angry or surprised, it shoots flames out of its back.'),
(156, 'Quilava', 10, NULL, 0.9, 19.0, 'Volcano', 'Before battle, it turns its back on its opponent to demonstrate how ferociously its fire blazes.'),
(157, 'Typhlosion', 10, NULL, 1.7, 79.5, 'Volcano', 'It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur to cause huge explosions.'),
(158, 'Totodile', 11, NULL, 0.6, 9.5, 'Big Jaw', 'Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.'),
(159, 'Croconaw', 11, NULL, 1.1, 25.0, 'Big Jaw', 'The tips of its fangs are slanted backward. Once those fangs clamp down, the prey has no hope of escape.'),
(160, 'Feraligatr', 11, NULL, 2.3, 88.8, 'Big Jaw', 'When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.'),
(161, 'Sentret', 1, NULL, 0.8, 6.0, 'Scout', 'This Pokémon is extremely cautious. Its supple tail is well muscled and firm to the touch.'),
(162, 'Furret', 1, NULL, 1.8, 32.5, 'Long Body', 'It raises its offspring inside a long, narrow nest. Once they''re old enough, it takes them outside the nest to prepare them for independence.'),
(163, 'Hoothoot', 1, 3, 0.7, 21.2, 'Owl', 'Hoothoot''s internal clock is precise at all times. It tilts its head in a fixed rhythm.'),
(164, 'Noctowl', 1, 3, 1.6, 40.8, 'Owl', 'Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.'),
(165, 'Ledyba', 7, 3, 1.0, 10.8, 'Five Star', 'This Pokémon is very sensitive to cold. In the warmth of Alola, it appears quite lively.'),
(166, 'Ledian', 7, 3, 1.4, 35.6, 'Five Star', 'It''s said that the patterns on its back are related to the stars in the night sky, but the details of that relationship remain unclear.'),
(167, 'Spinarak', 7, 4, 0.5, 8.5, 'String Spit', 'Even while there are prey ensnared in its nest of spun thread, Spinarak will wait motionlessly until darkness falls.'),
(168, 'Ariados', 7, 4, 1.1, 33.5, 'Long Leg', 'A single strand of a special thread is endlessly spun out of its rear. The thread leads back to its nest.'),
(169, 'Crobat', 4, 3, 1.8, 75.0, 'Bat', 'Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound, Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target''s neck.'),
(170, 'Chinchou', 11, 13, 0.5, 12.0, 'Angler', 'It lives in ocean depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.'),
(171, 'Lanturn', 11, 13, 1.2, 22.5, 'Light', 'Portions of its dorsal fin mutated, becoming the parts that glow brightly to lure prey.'),
(172, 'Pichu', 13, NULL, 0.3, 2.0, 'Tiny Mouse', 'It is unskilled at storing electric power. Any kind of shock causes it to discharge energy spontaneously.'),
(173, 'Cleffa', 18, NULL, 0.3, 3.0, 'Star Shape', 'On late nights illuminated by shooting stars, it gazes intently skyward, as if thinking of its home.'),
(174, 'Igglybuff', 1, 18, 0.3, 1.0, 'Balloon', 'Its body has a faintly sweet scent and is bouncy and soft. If it bounces even once, it cannot stop.'),
(175, 'Togepi', 18, NULL, 0.3, 1.5, 'Spike Ball', 'The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.'),
(176, 'Togetic', 18, 3, 0.6, 3.2, 'Happiness', 'They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.'),
(177, 'Natu', 14, 3, 0.2, 2.0, 'Tiny Bird', 'It is extremely good at climbing tree trunks and likes to eat the new sprouts on the trees.'),
(178, 'Xatu', 14, 3, 1.5, 15.0, 'Mystic', 'They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.'),
(179, 'Mareep', 13, NULL, 0.6, 7.8, 'Wool', 'If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.'),
(180, 'Flaffy', 13, NULL, 0.8, 13.3, 'Wool', 'As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won''t grow.'),
(181, 'Ampharos', 13, NULL, 1.4, 61.5, 'Light', 'The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.'),
(182, 'Bellossom', 12, NULL, 0.4, 5.8, 'Flower', 'Due to the effects of the Sun Stone, it is now active during the daytime. It likes to dance in pools of sunlight.'),
(183, 'Marill', 11, 18, 0.4, 8.5, 'Aqua Mouse', 'The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry even when it plays in the water.'),
(184, 'Azumarill', 11, 18, 0.8, 28.5, 'Aqua Rabbit', 'Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.'),
(185, 'Sudowoodo', 6, NULL, 1.2, 38.0, 'Imitation', 'Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.'),
(186, 'Politoed', 11, NULL, 1.1, 33.9, 'Frog', 'If Poliwag and Poliwhirl hear its echoing cry, they respond by gathering from far and wide.'),
(187, 'Hoppip', 12, 3, 0.4, 0.5, 'Cottonweed', 'This Pokémon is blown across vast distances by the wind. It is unclear where the Hoppip of Paldea originally came from.'),
(188, 'Skiploom', 12, 3, 0.6, 1.0, 'Cottonweed', 'Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the flower on the Pokémon''s head.'),
(189, 'Jumpluff', 12, 3, 0.8, 3.0, 'Cottonweed', 'Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its cotton spores run out, its journey ends, as does its life.'),
(190, 'Aipom', 1, NULL, 0.8, 11.5, 'Long Tail', 'It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.'),
(191, 'Sunkern', 12, NULL, 0.3, 1.8, 'Seed', 'It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. Knowing it''s weak, it simply feeds until it evolves.'),
(192, 'Sunflora', 12, NULL, 0.8, 8.5, 'Sun', 'In the daytime, it rushes about in a hectic manner, but it comes to a complete stop when the sun sets.'),
(193, 'Yanma', 7, 3, 1.2, 38.0, 'Clear Wing', 'As Yanma surveys its territory, it periodically stops to hover in place by flapping its wings at high speeds.'),
(194, 'Wooper', 11, 5, 0.4, 8.5, 'Water Fish', 'A transparent mucous membrane covers its body. Touching it bare-handed will cause a tingling numbness.'),
(195, 'Quagsire', 11, 5, 1.4, 75.0, 'Water Fish', 'This carefree Pokémon has an easygoing nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.'),
(196, 'Espeon', 14, NULL, 0.9, 26.5, 'Sun', 'The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is predicting its opponent''s next move.'),
(197, 'Umbreon', 17, NULL, 1.0, 27.0, 'Moonlight', 'When exposed to the moon''s aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.'),
(198, 'Murkrow', 17, 3, 0.5, 2.1, 'Darkness', 'Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.'),
(199, 'Slowking', 11, 14, 2.0, 79.5, 'Royal', 'When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke''s head and unlocked an extraordinary power.'),
(200, 'Misdreavus', 8, NULL, 0.7, 1.0, 'Screech', 'This Pokémon startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.'),
(201, 'Unknown', 14, NULL, 0.5, 5.0, 'Symbol', 'This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.'),
(202, 'Wobbuffet', 14, NULL, 1.3, 28.5, 'Patient', 'It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to pump up its counterstrike.'),
(203, 'Girafarig', 1, 14, 1.5, 41.5, 'Long Neck', 'Though very small, the brain in its tail is still considered an important organ because it emits powerful psychic energy.'),
(204, 'Pineco', 7, NULL, 0.6, 7.2, 'Bagworm', 'It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn''t bother it.'),
(205, 'Forretress', 7, 9, 1.2, 125.8, 'Bagworm', 'It''s usually found hanging on to a fat tree trunk. It shoots out bits of its shell when it sees action.'),
(206, 'Dunsparce', 1, NULL, 1.5, 14.0, 'Land Snake', 'It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.'),
(207, 'Gligar', 5, 3, 1.1, 64.8, 'Fly Scorpion', 'It builds its nest on a steep cliff. When it is done gliding, it hops along the ground back to its nest.'),
(208, 'Steelix', 9, 5, 9.2, 400.0, 'Iron Snake', 'It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.'),
(209, 'Snubbull', 18, NULL, 0.6, 7.8, 'Fairy', 'In truth, it is a cowardly Pokémon. It growls eagerly in order to hide its fear from its opponent.'),
(210, 'Granbull', 18, NULL, 1.4, 48.7, 'Fairy', 'It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked, it desperately flails its limbs about in an attempt to repel its opponent.'),
(211, 'Qwilfish', 11, 4, 0.5, 3.9, 'Balloon', 'Be cautious if this Pokémon starts sucking in water—it will soon attack by scattering the toxic spikes that grow all over its body.'),
(212, 'Scizor', 7, 9, 1.8, 118.0, 'Pincer', 'This Pokémon''s pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object they get ahold of into bits.'),
(213, 'Shuckle', 7, 6, 0.6, 20.5, 'Mold', 'It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.'),
(214, 'Heracross', 7, 2, 1.5, 54.0, 'Single Horn', 'It loves sweet nectar. To keep all the nectar to itself, it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.'),
(215, 'Sneasel', 17, 15, 0.9, 28.0, 'Sharp Claw', 'This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of darkness, waiting to attack its prey.'),
(216, 'Teddiursa', 1, NULL, 0.6, 8.8, 'Little Bear', 'This Pokémon discreetly follows Combee to find their hive. It scoops up big dollops of honey in its palms to eat.'),
(217, 'Ursaring', 1, NULL, 1.8, 125.8, 'Hibernator', 'It usually wears a hardened expression, but when it''s licking up honey—which it loves—the joy it feels will cause it to break into a wide grin.'),
(218, 'Slugma', 10, NULL, 0.7, 35.0, 'Lava', 'Its lava body can cool and chip away at times, but a magma bath will heal it right up.'),
(219, 'Magcargo', 10, 6, 0.8, 55.0, 'Lava', 'This Pokémon lives near the craters of volcanoes. It stores fire energy in its shell of cooled and hardened magma.'),
(220, 'Swinub', 15, 5, 0.4, 6.5, 'Pig', 'It searches for food by digging into the ground with its snout. Even frozen ground doesn''t give it any trouble.'),
(221, 'Piloswine', 15, 5, 1.1, 55.8, 'Swine', 'Covered by a shaggy coat, it is resistant to the cold. Its tusks of ice thicken when it snows.'),
(222, 'Corsola', 11, 6, 0.6, 5.0, 'Coral', 'Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can''t live in polluted waters.'),
(223, 'Remoraid', 11, NULL, 0.6, 12.0, 'Jet', 'The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.'),
(224, 'Octillery', 11, NULL, 0.9, 28.5, 'Jet', 'It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.'),
(225, 'Delibird', 15, 3, 0.9, 16.0, 'Delivery', 'It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by the food it had.'),
(226, 'Mantine', 11, 3, 2.1, 220.0, 'Kite', 'If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.'),
(227, 'Skarmory', 9, 3, 1.7, 50.5, 'Armor Bird', 'Its sturdy, heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.'),
(228, 'Houndour', 17, 10, 0.6, 10.8, 'Dark', 'It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.'),
(229, 'Houndoom', 17, 10, 1.9, 35.0, 'Dark', 'If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.'),
(230, 'Kingdra', 11, 16, 1.8, 152.0, 'Dragon', 'It sleeps deep on the ocean floor to build its energy. It is said to cause tornadoes as it wakes.'),
(231, 'Phanpy', 5, NULL, 0.5, 33.5, 'Long Nose', 'This Pokémon lives and nests on a riverbank. After playing in the mud, it won''t be able to settle down unless it washes its body.'),
(232, 'Donphan', 5, NULL, 1.1, 120.0, 'Armor', 'Donphan is covered in tough hide, so even being hit by a car won''t faze this Pokémon. However, it is extremely susceptible to rain.'),
(233, 'Porygon2', 1, NULL, 0.6, 32.5, 'Virtual', 'This artificial Pokémon evolved thanks to cutting-edge science. It sometimes displays behavior that is not in its programming.'),
(234, 'Stantler', 1, NULL, 1.4, 71.2, 'Big Horn', 'This Pokémon apparently used to live in much harsher environments, and thus it once had stronger psychic powers than it does now.'),
(235, 'Smeargle', 1, NULL, 1.2, 58.0, 'Painter', 'Once a Smeargle reaches adulthood, it will have other members of its species leave paw prints on its back.'),
(236, 'Tyrogue', 2, NULL, 0.7, 21.0, 'Scuffle', 'This earnest Pokémon battles all sorts of opponents, searching for the fighting style that suits it best.'),
(237, 'Hitmontop', 2, NULL, 1.4, 48.0, 'Handstand', 'This Pokémon is adept at dance-like kicks. The horn atop its head is made from the same substance that generally forms fur and claws.'),
(238, 'Smoochum', 15, 14, 0.4, 6.0, 'Kiss', 'If its face gets even slightly dirty, Smoochum will bathe immediately. But if its body gets dirty, Smoochum doesn''t really seem to care.'),
(239, 'Elekid', 13, NULL, 0.6, 23.5, 'Electric', 'It loves violent thunder. The space between its horns flickers bluish white when it is charging energy.'),
(240, 'Magby', 10, NULL, 0.7, 21.4, 'Live Coal', 'Each and every time it inhales and exhales, sparks leak from its mouth and nostrils.'),
(241, 'Miltank', 1, NULL, 1.2, 75.5, 'Milk Cow', 'Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it''s been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.'),
(242, 'Blissey', 1, NULL, 1.5, 46.8, 'Happiness', 'Anyone who takes even one taste of Blissey''s egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant to everyone.'),
(243, 'Raikou', 13, NULL, 1.9, 178.0, 'Thunder', 'Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.'),
(244, 'Entei', 10, NULL, 2.1, 198.0, 'Volcano', 'Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.'),
(245, 'Suicune', 11, NULL, 2.0, 187.0, 'Aurora', 'Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.'),
(246, 'Larvitar', 6, 5, 0.6, 72.0, 'Rock Skin', 'Born deep underground, this Pokémon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.'),
(247, 'Pupitar', 6, 5, 1.2, 105.6, 'Hard Shell', 'This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.'),
(248, 'Tyranitar', 6, 17, 2.0, 202.0, 'Armor', 'Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn''t care about others.'),
(249, 'Lugia', 14, 3, 5.2, 216.0, 'Diving', 'Lugia''s wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.'),
(250, 'Ho-oh', 10, 3, 3.8, 199.0, 'Rainbow', 'Ho-Oh''s feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.'),
(251, 'Celebi', 14, 12, 0.6, 5.0, 'Time Travel', 'This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.'),
(252, 'Treecko', 12, NULL, 0.5, 5.0, 'Wood Gecko', 'The small hooks on the soles of its feet latch on to walls and ceilings, so it will never fall even while hanging upside down.'),
(253, 'Grovyle', 12, NULL, 0.9, 21.6, 'Wood Gecko', 'Its strongly developed thigh muscles give it astounding agility and jumping performance.'),
(254, 'Sceptile', 12, NULL, 1.7, 52.2, 'Forest', 'It agilely flits through the jungle and uses the sharp-edged leaves on its arms to cut down its prey.'),
(255, 'Torchic', 10, NULL, 0.4, 2.5, 'Chick', 'Torchic feels toasty warm if you hug it. It has a flame sac inside its belly, and the flames burn continuously as long as Torchic has life in it.'),
(256, 'Combusken', 10, 2, 0.9, 19.5, 'Young Fowl', 'It boosts its concentration by emitting harsh cries. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.'),
(257, 'Blaziken', 10, 2, 1.9, 52.0, 'Blaze', 'When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.'),
(258, 'Mudkip', 11, NULL, 0.4, 7.6, 'Mud Fish', 'It has the power to crush large boulders into pieces. To rest, it buries itself in mud at the bottom of a river.'),
(259, 'Marshtomp', 11, 5, 0.7, 28.0, 'Mud Fish', 'Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has served to train its lower body and caused it to develop sturdy legs.'),
(260, 'Swampert', 11, 5, 1.5, 81.9, 'Mud Fish', 'Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing, it can break an enormous boulder into pieces.'),
(261, 'Poochyena', 17, NULL, 0.5, 13.6, 'Bite', 'It bares its large fangs and barks vigorously to try to intimidate opponents, but this is actually a manifestation of its cowardly nature.'),
(262, 'Mightyena', 17, NULL, 1.0, 37.0, 'Bite', 'They faithfully follow the orders of their leader. Prey targeted by Mightyena is never allowed to escape the outstanding teamwork of its pursuers.'),
(263, 'Zigzagoon', 1, NULL, 0.4, 17.5, 'Tiny Raccoon', 'It walks in zigzag fashion. It''s good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.'),
(264, 'Linoone', 1, NULL, 0.5, 32.5, 'Rushing', 'It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.'),
(265, 'Wurmple', 7, NULL, 0.3, 3.6, 'Worm', 'Using the spikes on its rear end, Wurmple peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This Pokémon''s feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.'),
(266, 'Silcoon', 7, NULL, 0.6, 10.0, 'Cocoon', 'Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There, this Pokémon hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.'),
(267, 'Beautifly', 7, 3, 1.0, 28.4, 'Butterfly', 'Beautifly''s favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this Pokémon, just leave a potted flower by an open window. Beautifly is sure to come looking for pollen.'),
(268, 'Cascoon', 7, NULL, 0.7, 11.5, 'Cocoon', 'Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This Pokémon prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.'),
(269, 'Dustox', 7, 4, 1.2, 31.6, 'Poison Moth', 'Dustox is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this Pokémon are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.'),
(270, 'Lotad', 11, 12, 0.5, 2.6, 'Water Weed', 'The leaf on its head is naturally dirt repellent and will stay clean even after transporting Pokémon that are covered in mud.'),
(271, 'Lombre', 11, 12, 1.2, 32.5, 'Jolly', 'Old folklore in Kitakami tells of a mischievous child who was reborn as a Pokémon.'),
(272, 'Ludicolo', 11, 12, 1.5, 55.0, 'Carefree', 'There are structures throughout its whole body that produce energy when hit by sound waves with a cheerful rhythm.'),
(273, 'Seedot', 12, NULL, 0.5, 4.0, 'Acorn', 'To expand its habitat, it pretends to be a nut so that bird Pokémon will pick it up and carry it far away.'),
(274, 'Nuzleaf', 12, 17, 1.0, 28.0, 'Wily', 'It leads a quiet life deep in the forest. If anything wanders into its territory, Nuzleaf will warn the intruder by sounding its grass flute.'),
(275, 'Shiftry', 12, 17, 1.3, 59.6, 'Wicked', 'It is said that when Shiftry flaps its leafy fans atop ancient trees, chilly winds blow and the season rolls into winter.'),
(276, 'Taillow', 1, 3, 0.3, 2.3, 'Tiny Swallow', 'Taillow courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy Pokémon will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.'),
(277, 'Swellow', 1, 3, 0.7, 19.8, 'Swallow', 'Swellow flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This Pokémon dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by Swellow''s clawed feet, preventing escape.'),
(278, 'Wingull', 11, 3, 0.6, 9.5, 'Seagull', 'It soars high in the sky, riding on updrafts like a glider. It carries food tucked in its bill.'),
(279, 'Pelipper', 11, 3, 1.2, 28.0, 'Water Bird', 'It is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon in its beak. It bobs on the waves to rest its wings.'),
(280, 'Ratls', 14, 18, 0.4, 6.6, 'Feeling', 'The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people''s emotions.'),
(281, 'Kirlia', 14, 18, 0.8, 20.2, 'Emotion', 'It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.'),
(282, 'Gardevoir', 14, 18, 1.6, 48.4, 'Embrace', 'To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.'),
(283, 'Surskit', 7, 11, 0.5, 1.7, 'Pond Skater', 'They usually live on ponds, but after an evening shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.'),
(284, 'Masquerain', 7, 3, 0.8, 2.6, 'Eyeball', 'It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction—to and fro and sideways.'),
(285, 'Shroomish', 12, NULL, 0.4, 4.5, 'Mushroom', 'It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.'),
(286, 'Breloom', 12, 2, 1.2, 39.2, 'Mushroom', 'It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.'),
(287, 'Slakoth', 1, NULL, 0.8, 24.0, 'Slaker', 'It sleeps for 20 hours every day. Making drowsy those that see it is one of its abilities.'),
(288, 'Vigoroth', 1, NULL, 1.4, 46.5, 'Wild Monkey', 'Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.'),
(289, 'Slaking', 1, NULL, 2.0, 130.5, 'Lazy', 'It is the world''s most slothful Pokémon. However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.'),
(290, 'Nincada', 7, 5, 0.5, 5.5, 'Trainee', 'Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.'),
(291, 'Ninjask', 7, 3, 0.8, 12.0, 'Ninja', 'Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.'),
(292, 'Shedinja', 7, 8, 0.8, 1.2, 'Shed', 'A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.'),
(293, 'Whismur', 1, NULL, 0.6, 16.3, 'Whisper', 'The cry of a Whismur is over 100 decibels. If you''re close to a Whismur when it lets out a cry, you''ll be stuck with an all-day headache.'),
(294, 'Loudred', 1, NULL, 1.0, 40.5, 'Big Voice', 'Loudred''s ears serve as speakers, and they can put out sound waves powerful enough to blow away a house.'),
(295, 'Exploud', 1, NULL, 1.5, 84.0, 'Loud Noise', 'In the past, people would use the loud voices of these Pokémon as a means of communication between distant cities.'),
(296, 'Makuhita', 2, NULL, 1.0, 86.4, 'Guts', 'It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.'),
(297, 'Hariyama', 2, NULL, 2.3, 253.8, 'Arm Thrust', 'It loves challenging others to tests of strength. It has the power to stop a train with a slap.'),
(298, 'Azurill', 1, 18, 0.2, 2.0, 'Polka Dot', 'Its tail bounces like a rubber ball. It flings that tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.'),
(299, 'Nosepass', 6, NULL, 1.0, 97.0, 'Compass', 'The magnet in Nosepass''s nose provides an unerring compass, making this Pokémon an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.'),
(300, 'Skitty', 1, NULL, 0.6, 11.0, 'Kitten', 'Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This Pokémon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.'),
(301, 'Delcatty', 1, NULL, 1.1, 32.6, 'Prim', 'Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this Pokémon eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.'),
(302, 'Sableye', 17, 8, 0.5, 11.0, 'Darkness', 'It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.'),
(303, 'Mawile', 9, 18, 0.6, 11.5, 'Deceiver', 'It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.'),
(304, 'Aron', 9, 6, 0.4, 60.0, 'Iron Armor', 'It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks— to build up the steel armor that protects its body.'),
(305, 'Lairon', 9, 6, 0.9, 120.0, 'Iron Armor', 'Lairon live in mountains brimming with spring water and iron ore, so these Pokémon often came into conflict with humans in the past.'),
(306, 'Aggron', 9, 6, 2.1, 360.0, 'Iron Armor', 'Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.'),
(307, 'Meditite', 2, 14, 0.6, 11.2, 'Meditate', 'It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.'),
(308, 'Medicham', 2, 14, 1.3, 31.5, 'Meditate', 'Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe''s next move.'),
(309, 'Electrike', 13, NULL, 0.6, 15.2, 'Lightning', 'It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.'),
(310, 'Manetric', 13, NULL, 1.5, 40.2, 'Discharge', 'It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.'),
(311, 'Plusle', 13, NULL, 0.4, 4.2, 'Cheering', 'It cheers on partners while scattering sparks from its body. It climbs telephone poles to absorb electricity.'),
(312, 'Minun', 13, NULL, 0.4, 4.2, 'Cheering', 'Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.'),
(313, 'Volbeat', 7, NULL, 0.7, 17.7, 'Firefly', 'It lives around clean ponds. At night, its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.'),
(314, 'Illumise', 7, NULL, 0.6, 17.7, 'Firefly', 'Illumise uses its sweet scent to guide Volbeat, having them form over 200 patterns in the night sky.'),
(315, 'Roselia', 12, 4, 0.3, 2.0, 'Thorn', 'Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.'),
(316, 'Gulpin', 4, NULL, 0.4, 10.3, 'Stomach', 'There is nothing its stomach can''t digest. While it is digesting, vile, overpowering gases are expelled.'),
(317, 'Swalot', 4, NULL, 1.7, 80.0, 'Poison Bag', 'It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.'),
(318, 'Carvanha', 11, 17, 0.8, 20.8, 'Savage', 'It won''t attack while it''s alone—not even if it spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to join it, and then the Pokémon attack as a group.'),
(319, 'Sharpedo', 11, 17, 1.8, 88.8, 'Brutal', 'As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.'),
(320, 'Wailmer', 11, NULL, 2.0, 130.0, 'Ball Whale', 'It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.'),
(321, 'Wailord', 11, NULL, 14.5, 398.0, 'Float Whale', 'It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.'),
(322, 'Numel', 10, 5, 0.7, 24.0, 'Numb', 'Magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. When it grows cold, the magma hardens and slows it.'),
(323, 'Camerupt', 10, 5, 1.9, 220.0, 'Eruption', 'It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.'),
(324, 'Torkoal', 10, NULL, 0.5, 80.4, 'Coal', 'It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.'),
(325, 'Spoink', 14, NULL, 0.7, 30.6, 'Bounce', 'Spoink will die if it stops bouncing. The pearl on its head amplifies its psychic powers.'),
(326, 'Grumpig', 14, NULL, 0.9, 71.5, 'Manipulate', 'It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.'),
(327, 'Spinda', 1, NULL, 1.1, 5.0, 'Spot Panda', 'Its steps are shaky and stumbling. Walking for a long time makes it feel sick.'),
(328, 'Trapinch', 5, NULL, 0.7, 15.0, 'Ant Pit', 'This Pokémon lives in arid deserts. It patiently awaits prey inside its funnel-shaped nest.'),
(329, 'Vibrava', 5, 16, 1.1, 15.3, 'Vibration', 'Rather than using its underdeveloped wings for flight, it rubs them together, emitting ultrasonic waves to attack its enemies.'),
(330, 'Flygon', 5, 16, 2.0, 82.0, 'Mystic', 'Known as the Desert Spirit, this Pokémon hides in the sandstorms it causes by beating its wings.'),
(331, 'Cacnea', 12, NULL, 0.4, 51.3, 'Cactus', 'It prefers harsh environments, such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.'),
(332, 'Cacturne', 12, 17, 1.3, 77.4, 'Scarecrow', 'Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.'),
(333, 'Swablu', 1, 3, 0.4, 1.2, 'Cotton Bird', 'It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.'),
(334, 'Altaria', 16, 3, 1.1, 20.6, 'Humming', 'If it bonds with a person, it will gently envelop the friend with its soft wings, then hum.'),
(335, 'Zangoose', 1, NULL, 1.3, 40.3, 'Cat Ferret', 'It''s Seviper''s archrival. To threaten those it encounters, it fans out the claws on its front paws.'),
(336, 'Seviper', 4, NULL, 2.7, 52.5, 'Fang Snake', 'It sharpens its swordlike tail on hard rocks. It hides in tall grass and strikes unwary prey with venomous fangs.'),
(337, 'Lunatone', 6, 14, 1.0, 168.0, 'Meteorite', 'The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It''s active on the night of a full moon.'),
(338, 'Solrock', 6, 14, 1.2, 154.0, 'Meteorite', 'When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.'),
(339, 'Barboach', 11, 5, 0.4, 1.9, 'Whiskers', 'Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey''s location.'),
(340, 'Whiscash', 11, 5, 0.9, 23.6, 'Whiskers', 'It is extremely protective of its territory. If any foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.'),
(341, 'Corphish', 11, NULL, 0.6, 11.5, 'Ruffian', 'It came from overseas. It is a very hardy creature that will quickly proliferate, even in polluted streams.'),
(342, 'Crawdaunt', 11, 17, 1.1, 32.8, 'Rogue', 'Loving to battle, this Pokémon pinches all Pokémon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.'),
(343, 'Baltoy', 5, 14, 0.5, 21.5, 'Clay Doll', 'It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.'),
(344, 'Claydol', 5, 14, 1.5, 108.0, 'Clay Doll', 'This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.'),
(345, 'Lileep', 6, 12, 1.0, 23.8, 'Sea Lily', 'This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.'),
(346, 'Cradily', 6, 12, 1.5, 60.4, 'Barnacle', 'It has short legs and can''t walk very fast, but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.'),
(347, 'Anorith', 6, 7, 0.7, 12.5, 'Old Shrimp', 'This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Anorith lived in the ocean about 100,000,000 years ago, hunting with its pair of claws.'),
(348, 'Armaldo', 6, 7, 1.5, 68.2, 'Plate', 'After evolution, this Pokémon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger, and blows from its tail are devastating.'),
(349, 'Feebas', 11, NULL, 0.6, 7.4, 'Fish', 'This tough Pokémon is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn''t popular.'),
(350, 'Milotic', 11, NULL, 6.2, 162.0, 'Tender', 'Its lovely scales are described as rainbow-colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.'),
(351, 'Castform', 1, NULL, 0.3, 0.8, 'Weather', 'Although its form changes with the weather, that is apparently the result of a chemical reaction and not the result of its own free will.'),
(352, 'Kecleon', 1, NULL, 1.0, 22.0, 'Color Swap', 'It changes its hue to blend into its surroundings. If no one takes notice of it for too long, it will pout and never reveal itself.'),
(353, 'Shuppet', 8, NULL, 0.6, 2.3, 'Puppet', 'It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice. Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.'),
(354, 'Banette', 8, NULL, 1.1, 12.5, 'Marionette', 'This Pokémon developed from an abandoned doll that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.'),
(355, 'Duskull', 8, NULL, 0.8, 15.0, 'Requiem', 'In the dead of night, these Pokémon wander through towns in search of children, whose vital energy is a Duskull''s favorite food.'),
(356, 'Dusclops', 8, NULL, 1.6, 30.6, 'Beckon', 'Dusclops is feared because it''s said to pull the soul out of anyone who gazes upon the strange movements of its hands.'),
(357, 'Tropius', 12, 3, 2.0, 100.0, 'Fruit', 'It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows twice a year.'),
(358, 'Chimecho', 14, NULL, 0.6, 1.0, 'Wind Chime', 'It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.'),
(359, 'Absol', 17, NULL, 1.2, 47.0, 'Disaster', 'Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.'),
(360, 'Wynaut', 14, NULL, 0.6, 14.0, 'Bright', 'It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.'),
(361, 'Snorunt', 15, NULL, 0.7, 16.8, 'Snow Hat', 'It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.'),
(362, 'Glalie', 15, NULL, 1.5, 256.5, 'Face', 'Its prey is instantaneously frozen stiff by the cold air it exhales from its huge mouth. While they''re in that frozen state, it gobbles them up.'),
(363, 'Spheal', 15, 11, 0.8, 39.5, 'Clap', 'This Pokémon''s body is covered in blubber and impressively round. It''s faster for Spheal to roll around than walk.'),
(364, 'Sealeo', 15, 11, 1.1, 87.6, 'Ball Roll', 'Sealeo live on top of drift ice. They go swimming when they''re on the hunt, seeking out their prey by scent.'),
(365, 'Walrein', 15, 11, 1.4, 150.6, 'Ice Break', 'Walrein form herds of 20 to 30 individuals. When a threat appears, the herd''s leader will protect the group with its life.'),
(366, 'Clamperl', 11, NULL, 0.4, 52.5, 'Bivalve', 'Despite its appearance, it''s carnivorous. It clamps down on its prey with both sides of its shell and doesn''t let go until they stop moving.'),
(367, 'Huntail', 11, NULL, 1.7, 27.0, 'Deep Sea', 'It''s not the strongest swimmer. It wags its tail to lure in its prey and then gulps them down as soon as they get close.'),
(368, 'Gorebyss', 11, NULL, 1.8, 22.6, 'South Sea', 'The color of its body changes with the water temperature. The coloration of Gorebyss in Alola is almost blindingly vivid.'),
(369, 'Relicanth', 11, 6, 1.0, 23.4, 'Longevity', 'Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.'),
(370, 'Luvdisc', 11, NULL, 0.6, 8.7, 'Rendezvous', 'Its heart-shaped body makes it popular. In some places, you would give a Luvdisc to someone you love.'),
(371, 'Bagon', 16, NULL, 0.6, 42.1, 'Rock Head', 'Its steel-hard head can shatter boulders. It longingly hopes for wings to grow so it can fly.'),
(372, 'Shelgon', 16, NULL, 1.1, 110.5, 'Endurance', 'The cells within its shell transform with explosive speed, preparing it for evolution.'),
(373, 'Salamance', 16, 3, 1.5, 102.6, 'Dragon', 'It flies around on its wings, which have grown in at last. In its happiness, it gushes hot flames, burning up everything it passes over.'),
(374, 'Beldum', 9, 14, 0.6, 95.2, 'Iron Ball', 'The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground''s natural magnetism, letting it float.'),
(375, 'Metang', 9, 14, 1.2, 202.5, 'Iron Claw', 'It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.'),
(376, 'Metagross', 9, 14, 1.6, 550.0, 'Iron Leg', 'It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.'),
(377, 'Regirock', 6, NULL, 1.7, 230.0, 'Rock Peak', 'Every bit of Regirock''s body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode, this Pokémon sticks rocks to itself to repair what''s been lost.'),
(378, 'Regice', 15, NULL, 1.8, 175.0, 'Iceberg', 'With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as -328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.'),
(379, 'Registeel', 9, NULL, 1.9, 205.0, 'Iron', 'Registeel''s body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.'),
(380, 'Latias', 16, 14, 1.4, 40.0, 'Eon', 'Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.'),
(381, 'Latios', 16, 14, 2.0, 60.0, 'Eon', 'Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.'),
(382, 'Kyogre', 11, NULL, 4.5, 352.0, 'Sea Basin', 'Through Primal Reversion and with nature''s full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.'),
(383, 'Groudon', 5, NULL, 3.5, 950.0, 'Continent', 'Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.'),
(384, 'Rayquaza', 16, 3, 7.0, 206.5, 'Sky High', 'Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.'),
(385, 'Jirachi', 9, 14, 0.3, 1.1, 'Wish', 'A legend states that Jirachi will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this Pokémon senses danger, it will fight without awakening.'),
(386, 'Deoxys', 14, NULL, 1.7, 60.8, 'DNA', 'The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokémon''s chest appears to be its brain.'),
(389, 'Torterra', 12, 5, 2.2, 310.0, 'Continent', 'Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground dwelt a gigantic Torterra.'),
(407, 'Roserade', 12, 4, 0.9, 14.5, 'Bouquet', 'After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.'),
(430, 'Honchkrow', 17, 3, 0.9, 27.3, 'Big Boss', 'It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.'),
(442, 'Spiritomb', 8, 17, 1.0, 108.0, 'Forbidden', 'Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.'),
(445, 'Garchomp', 16, 5, 1.9, 95.0, 'Mach', 'It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.'),
(448, 'Lucario', 2, 9, 1.2, 54.0, 'Aura', 'It''s said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario, since it can detect auras—even those of foes it could not otherwise see.'),
(461, 'Weavile', 17, 15, 1.1, 34.0, 'Sharp Claw', 'Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.'),
(468, 'Togekiss', 18, 3, 1.5, 38.0, 'Jubilee', 'These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they''ve hardly been seen at all.'),
(565, 'Carracosta', 11, 6, 1.2, 81.0, 'Prototurtle', 'Carracosta completely devours its prey—bones, shells, and all. Because of this, Carracosta''s own shell grows thick and sturdy.'),
(567, 'Archeops', 6, 3, 1.4, 32.0, 'First Bird', 'It needs a running start to take off. If Archeops wants to fly, it first needs to run nearly 25 mph, building speed over a course of about 2.5 miles.'),
(571, 'Zoroark', 17, NULL, 1.6, 81.1, 'Illusion Fox', 'Stories say those who tried to catch Zoroark were trapped in an illusion and punished.'),
(584, 'Vanilluxe', 15, NULL, 1.3, 57.5, 'Snowstorm', 'When its anger reaches a breaking point, this Pokémon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes every creature around it, be they friend or foe.'),
(601, 'Klinklang', 9, NULL, 0.6, 81.0, 'Gear', 'From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.'),
(612, 'Haxorus', 16, NULL, 1.8, 105.5, 'Axe Jaw', 'This Pokémon nests in caves and abandoned mines. It is docile, but it will become incredibly angry if its tusks are touched, so beware.'),
(621, 'Druddigon', 16, NULL, 1.6, 139.0, 'Cave', 'Druddigon lives in caves, but it never skips sunbathing—it won''t be able to move if its body gets too cold.'),
(635, 'Hydreigon', 17, 16, 1.8, 160.0, 'Brutal', 'Only the central head has a brain. It is very intelligent, but it thinks only of destruction.'),
(643, 'Reshiram', 16, 10, 3.2, 330.0, 'Vast White', 'This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.'),
(658, 'Greninja', 11, 17, 1.5, 40.0, 'Ninja', 'The movement of air against the long tongue Greninja keeps wrapped around its neck allows it to sense enemies it can''t see.'),
(681, 'Aegislash', 9, 8, 1.7, 53.0, 'Royal Sword', 'In this defensive stance, Aegislash uses its steel body and a force field of spectral power to reduce the damage of any attack.'),
(697, 'Tyrantrum', 6, 16, 2.5, 270.0, 'Despot', 'This Pokémon is from about 100,000,000 years ago. It has the presence of a king, vicious but magnificent.'),
(699, 'Aurorus', 6, 15, 2.7, 225.0, 'Tundra', 'Aurorus was restored from a fossil. It''s said that when this Pokémon howls, auroras appear in the night sky.'),
(701, 'Hawlucha', 2, 3, 0.8, 21.5, 'Wrestling', 'Its elegant finishing moves—performed by nimbly leaping around using its wings—are polished in the forest where it was born and raised.'),
(706, 'Goodra', 16, NULL, 2.0, 150.5, 'Dragon', 'It loves the rain. This mellow Pokémon can be seen walking around on the plains and in the mountains on rainy days.'),
(711, 'Gourgeist', 8, 12, 0.9, 12.5, 'Pumpkin', 'Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.'),
(818, 'Inteleon', 11, NULL, 1.9, 45.2, 'Secret Agent', 'It uses special lenses in its eyes to sense things about its opponents—like their body heat—then attacks once it identifies a weak spot.'),
(865, 'Sirfetch''d', 2, NULL, 0.8, 117.0, 'Wild Duck', 'Only Farfetch''d that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon''s leek withers, it will retire from combat.'),
(866, 'Mr. Rime', 15, 14, 1.5, 58.2, 'Comedian', 'It''s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.'),
(882, 'Dracovish', 11, 16, 2.3, 150.0, 'Fossil', 'Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.'),
(887, 'Dragapult', 16, 8, 3.0, 50.0, 'Stealth', 'Dragapult can make its whole body transparent by clearing its mind and focusing. Even the Dreepy in Dragapult''s horns become invisible.');
